    {/* Energy flow diagram */}
    <div style={{ ...S.box, marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={{ ...S.lbl, marginBottom: 8, color: "#00ccaa" }}>ENERGY FLOW</div>
      {[
        { l: "Input Power", v: fmt(params.computePower_kW * 1000) + "W", c: "#ffffff", w: 100 },
        { l: "→ Useful Compute", v: fmt(params.computePower_kW * 1000 * params.efficiency) + "W", c: "#4488ff", w: params.efficiency * 100 },
        { l: "→ Waste Heat", v: fmt(bulk.P_waste) + "W", c: "#ff6644", w: (1 - params.efficiency) * 100 },
        { l: "  → Bulk Radiation", v: fmt(bulk.P_waste * (1 - params.hotSegmentFraction)) + "W", c: "#ff664488", w: (1 - params.efficiency) * (1 - params.hotSegmentFraction) * 100 },
        { l: "  → Hot Segment", v: fmt(geom.P_hot_total) + "W", c: "#ffaa44", w: Math.min(30, (geom.P_hot_total / (params.computePower_kW * 1000)) * 100) },
        { l: "    → Directed Beam", v: fmt(geom.P_directed_total) + "W", c: "#00ccaa", w: Math.min(15, (geom.P_directed_total / (params.computePower_kW * 1000)) * 100) },
        { l: "      → Received", v: fmt(mod.P_rx) + "W", c: "#00ffaa", w: Math.max(1, Math.min(10, (mod.P_rx / (params.computePower_kW * 1000)) * 1e6)) },
      ].map(({ l, v, c, w }) => (
        <div key={l} style={{ marginBottom: 4 }}>
          <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between", fontSize: 9, color: "#5a7a8a" }}>
            <span>{l}</span><span style={{ color: c, fontWeight: 600 }}>{v}</span>
          </div>
          <div style={{ height: 4, background: "#0a0e14", borderRadius: 2, overflow: "hidden" }}>
            <div style={{ width: `${Math.max(1, w)}%`, height: "100%", background: c, borderRadius: 2, transition: "width 0.3s" }} />
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    {/* Key metrics */}
    <div style={{ display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 1fr", gap: 6, marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={S.box}>
        <div style={S.lbl}>Channel Capacity</div>
        <div style={{ ...S.val, color: "#00ffaa" }}>{fmtBits(mod.capacity_bps)}</div>
        <div style={S.sub}>@ {params.switchRate_kHz} kHz switch</div>
      </div>
      <div style={S.box}>
        <div style={S.lbl}>Shannon Limit</div>
        <div style={{ ...S.val, color: "#4488ff" }}>{fmtBits(mod.shannonLimit)}</div>
        <div style={S.sub}>if full BW usable</div>
      </div>
      <div style={S.box}>
        <div style={S.lbl}>Dual-Use Mass</div>
        <div style={S.val}>{mod.dualUseMass.toFixed(1)} kg</div>
        <div style={S.sub}>horns + modulators</div>
      </div>
      <div style={S.box}>
        <div style={S.lbl}>Mod Power</div>
        <div style={S.val}>{mod.dualUsePower.toFixed(1)} W</div>
        <div style={S.sub}>{geom.N_horns} × {params.modPowerPerThroat_W}W</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Architecture note */}
    <div style={{
      background: "#00ccaa06", border: "1px solid #00ccaa20",
      borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", fontSize: 9, color: "#5a8a7a", lineHeight: 1.6,
    }}>
      <b style={{ color: "#00ccaa" }}>THERMOPYLAE ARCHITECTURE: </b>
      Bulk radiator does its thermal job unchanged. A small hot fraction ({(params.hotSegmentFraction * 100).toFixed(0)}%)
      runs at {params.hotSegmentTemp_K}K pushing emission to {geom.λ_emit_um.toFixed(1)}μm.
      Horn structures narrow the lobe to {geom.beamDiv_arcsec.toFixed(1)}″ — geometry does the
      beam-forming, not coherence. Active modulators at each throat gate the emission
      at {params.switchRate_kHz} kHz. Brightness capped at T_phys. Information rides the modulation,
      carrier power is free.
    </div>
  </>}

  {/* ─── LAYERS ─── */}
  {tab === "layers" && <>
    <div style={{ ...S.lbl, color: "#ff6644", marginBottom: 6 }}>LAYER 1: BULK RADIATOR</div>
    {L1_PARAMS.map(p => <Slider key={p.key} {...p} value={params[p.key]} onChange={setP} accent="#ff6644" />)}
    <div style={{ display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 1fr 1fr", gap: 4, marginBottom: 14 }}>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Area</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ff6644", fontWeight: 600 }}>{fmt(bulk.A_total, 0)}m²</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Mass</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ff6644", fontWeight: 600 }}>{fmt(bulk.mass_rad, 0)}kg</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>W/m²</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ff6644", fontWeight: 600 }}>{fmt(bulk.q_rad, 0)}</div></div>
    </div>

    <div style={{ ...S.lbl, color: "#ffaa44", marginBottom: 6 }}>LAYER 2: HORN CONCENTRATOR</div>
    {L2_PARAMS.map(p => <Slider key={p.key} {...p} value={params[p.key]} onChange={setP} accent="#ffaa44" />)}
    <div style={{ display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 1fr 1fr", gap: 4, marginBottom: 14 }}>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Horns</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ffaa44", fontWeight: 600 }}>{geom.N_horns}</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Beam</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ffaa44", fontWeight: 600 }}>{geom.beamDiv_arcsec.toFixed(1)}″</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>λ emit</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#ffaa44", fontWeight: 600 }}>{geom.λ_emit_um.toFixed(1)}μm</div></div>
    </div>

    <div style={{ ...S.lbl, color: "#00ccaa", marginBottom: 6 }}>LAYER 3: ACTIVE MODULATOR</div>
    {L3_PARAMS.map(p => <Slider key={p.key} {...p} value={params[p.key]} onChange={setP} accent="#00ccaa" />)}
    <div style={{ display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 1fr 1fr", gap: 4, marginBottom: 14 }}>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>SNR</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 600 }}>{mod.SNR_dB.toFixed(1)}dB</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Capacity</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 600 }}>{fmtBits(mod.capacity_bps)}</div></div>
      <div style={S.box}><div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a5a6a" }}>Rx Power</div><div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 600 }}>{fmt(mod.P_rx)}W</div></div>
    </div>
  </>}

  {/* ─── SWEEP ─── */}
  {tab === "sweep" && <>
    <div style={{ display: "flex", alignItems: "center", gap: 8, marginBottom: 8 }}>
      <span style={S.lbl}>SWEEP PARAM:</span>
      <select value={sweepKey} onChange={e => setSweepKey(e.target.value)}
        style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #1a2a3a", color: "#00ccaa", borderRadius: 4, padding: "3px 6px", fontSize: 9, fontFamily: "inherit" }}>
        {allParamDefs.map(p => <option key={p.key} value={p.key}>{p.label}</option>)}
      </select>
    </div>
    <MiniChart data={sweepData} xKey="x" yKey="capacity" xLabel={sweepDef.label} yLabel="Capacity bps" color="#00ccaa" highlight={params[sweepKey]} logY />
    <MiniChart data={sweepData} xKey="x" yKey="SNR_dB" xLabel={sweepDef.label} yLabel="SNR dB" color="#ffaa44" highlight={params[sweepKey]} />
    <MiniChart data={sweepData} xKey="x" yKey="P_rx" xLabel={sweepDef.label} yLabel="Rx Power W" color="#4488ff" highlight={params[sweepKey]} logY />

    <div style={{ marginTop: 10 }}>
      <Slider {...sweepDef} value={params[sweepKey]} onChange={setP} />
    </div>
  </>}

  {/* ─── COMPARE ─── */}
  {tab === "compare" && <>
    <div style={{ ...S.box, marginBottom: 10, borderColor: "#00ccaa30" }}>
      <div style={{ ...S.lbl, color: "#00ccaa", marginBottom: 8 }}>THERMOPYLAE vs 3m X-BAND DISH</div>
      <CompBar l1="IR Dual-Use" v1={mod.capacity_bps} l2="X-Band" v2={mod.xb_cap} c1="#00ccaa" c2="#ff6644" u={fmtBits} />
      <CompBar l1="IR SNR" v1={mod.SNR_dB} l2="X-Band SNR" v2={mod.xb_SNR_dB} c1="#00ccaa" c2="#ff6644" u={v => v.toFixed(1) + "dB"} />
      <CompBar l1="Overhead" v1={mod.dualUseMass} l2="Dedicated" v2={mod.xb_mass} c1="#00ccaa" c2="#ff6644" u={v => v.toFixed(0) + "kg"} />
      <CompBar l1="Power" v1={mod.dualUsePower} l2="TWTA" v2={mod.xb_power} c1="#00ccaa" c2="#ff6644" u={v => v.toFixed(0) + "W"} />
    </div>

    <div style={{ ...S.box, marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={{ ...S.lbl, marginBottom: 6 }}>MASS EFFICIENCY (bps/kg)</div>
      <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between", alignItems: "baseline" }}>
        <div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#4a6a7a" }}>Thermopylae</div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 15, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 700 }}>{fmtBits(mod.bpsPerKg_dual)}/kg</div>
        </div>
        <div style={{ textAlign: "right" }}>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#4a6a7a" }}>X-Band</div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 15, color: "#ff6644", fontWeight: 700 }}>{fmtBits(mod.bpsPerKg_xband)}/kg</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style={{
        marginTop: 8, fontSize: 11, textAlign: "center", fontWeight: 700,
        color: dualWin ? "#00ffaa" : "#ff6644",
      }}>
        {dualWin
          ? `THERMOPYLAE: saves ${mod.massSaved.toFixed(0)}kg = ${fmtCost(mod.massSaved * (params.radDensity_kgm2 > 0 ? 2700 : 2700))} launch`
          : `X-BAND WINS by ${(-mod.massSaved).toFixed(0)}kg`}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style={{ ...S.box, marginBottom: 10, fontSize: 9, color: "#5a8a7a", lineHeight: 1.6 }}>
      <b style={{ color: "#00ccaa" }}>REGIME MAP: </b>
      Thermopylae wins when you already have large radiator area (high compute waste heat),
      moderate distances (LEO/GEO), and can tolerate modest data rates.
      X-band wins for deep space, high data rate, or when radiator area is small.
      <br /><br />
      <b style={{ color: "#ffaa44" }}>HYBRID OPTION: </b>
      Use Thermopylae as a secondary/backup link, beacon, or telemetry channel.
      Reserve X-band for bulk data. The IR link costs almost nothing if the radiator exists —
      it's a free bonus channel on sunk mass.
    </div>

    <div style={{
      background: "#ff664408", border: "1px solid #ff664420",
      borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", fontSize: 9, color: "#7a5a4a", lineHeight: 1.6,
    }}>
      <b style={{ color: "#ff6644" }}>OPEN QUESTIONS: </b>
      Atmospheric windows at receiver wavelength. Thermal stability during modulation —
      does switching emissivity at kHz rates create thermal cycling fatigue?
      Horn alignment tolerance over structural flexing. Whether hot segment
      creates thermal gradient problems for adjacent compute hardware.
    </div>
  </>}

  <div style={{ fontSize: 7, color: "#1a2a3a", textAlign: "center", padding: 10 }}>
    Planck · Stefan-Boltzmann · Shannon-Hartley · Wien
  </div>
</div>
```

);
}
